message.content: cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY - The paper discusses a congestion control algorithm for data centers and long-distance networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and communication (cs.COMM). It also involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques (cs.IT) to improve TCP performance. The paper specifically focuses on data centers (cs.DC) and the challenges of high bandwidth-delay product networks, which is a common issue in data centers. Finally, the paper proposes a new congestion control algorithm that aims to improve network stability and efficiency, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
